    "When the threshold was corrected from 5 to 10% based on the findings of a previous study 4, the concordance level for the ISUP grade groups significantly improved for radical prostatectomy and consequently eliminated the differences in the concordance levels of the ISUP grade groups between biopsy cores and radical prostatectomy specimens.",
    "These conclusive findings emphasize the importance of adjusting the decision thresholds for a better consensus level between artificial intelligence and a pool of pathologists or even between pathologists.",
